    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I can reproduce this problem many times in a day. The loading spinner stays there forever and the code doesn't reload entirely. Then I need to re-save the file with a dummy whitespace or anything and then when I request shadow-cljs to reload again it picks up everything. It's a ceremony I got used to, but it sucks, and it existed since the first time I disabled auto hot-reload from shadow.\r\n\r\nI once tried to investigate and solve the problem, but gave up because I thought it was just me. I don't use hot reload in the sense of reloading on every file save, so that's why I thought this issue was just mine and never bothered reporting. I have the `SHADOW_AUTOBUILD_ENABLED` env var set to `false`.",
